```

Implementing the Fork and Exec logic...

The kernel only starts the YFS server as the init processâ€”the test program passed as argv[1] isn't automatically launched. Instead, YFS must fork a child process and execute the test program within it. My current main function completely ignores this requirement, which is why the test program never runs.

I also need to handle the deadlock detection case where Receive returns 0, indicating all processes are blocked waiting for messages. When that happens, the main loop should break out of its receive loop.

